dcterms:description: MiniImageNet is a subset of ImageNet designed for few-shot learning, containing 100 classes with 600 examples per class. It is commonly used as a benchmark for evaluating few-shot learning methods.
dcterms:title: MiniImageNet

dcterms:description: TieredImageNet is a large-scale dataset for few-shot learning, containing 351 training categories, 97 validation categories, and 160 test categories, providing a more challenging benchmark than MiniImageNet.
dcterms:title: TieredImageNet

dcterms:description: The Caltech-UCSD Birds-200-2011 (CUB) dataset is designed for fine-grained classification of bird species, containing 11,788 images across 200 species, with bounding box annotations for each image.
dcterms:title: Caltech-UCSD Birds-200-2011 (CUB)

dcterms:description: OfficeHome is a dataset for unsupervised domain adaptation, consisting of images from four domains: Art, Clipart, Product, and Real World, with a total of 15 classes per domain.
